DOS-PORT (patch 0081, Phase 9 wave 17.3-β).

Wave 17.2 (patch 0080) added a rendered-backdrop cache for the BK_*
scrolltypes that route through map_draw_backdrop's tile loop. The
title screen uses BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS scrolltype, which short-circuits
through DrawFastLeftLayered() before reaching the tile loop — so wave
17.2 doesn't engage on title and contributes 0 fps gain there.

This patch extends the same cache to the BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS branch.
The cache buffer (g_backdrop_cache_sfc) and key fields are shared with
patch 0080; scrolltype is part of the key so the two paths don't
collide. New helper _render_layered_to_surface() replicates
DrawFastLeftLayered's 5-layer + optional clear-color logic but writes
through raw SDL_BlitSurface (no Renderer overhead, no
SDL_RenderTexture queue flush — blitPatternAcross's slow path is what
makes the legacy renderer expensive on this scrolltype).

CRITICAL ANALYSIS — title screen has parscroll_x decrement EVERY
frame (per the existing
'if ((mode==NORMAL||mode==TITLE) && !frozen && !paused) --parscroll_x'
in DrawFastLeftLayered, now extracted to
_fastleft_layered_update_parscroll). The cache key includes
parscroll_x, so cache MISSES every frame on title (case b per the
team-lead's task description). The win therefore comes NOT from cache
hits but from the miss path being faster than the legacy path:

  Legacy: 5 layers × ~10 tiles/layer = ~50 SDL_RenderTexture calls,
          slow-path-queued, ~0.4 ms each = ~20 ms/flip on real HW.

  New (miss): same ~50 SDL_BlitSurface calls into cache (memcpy, no
          queue, ~0.05 ms each) + 1 cache→window SDL_BlitSurface
          (~0.3 ms) = ~3 ms/flip.

Net per-flip cost on title drops ~17 ms even with 0% hit rate.
On non-title BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS scenes (Outer Wall, Balcony) cache
hits when the player is paused — same ~17 ms saved per miss frame
plus near-zero cost on hit frames.

Killswitch: shared with wave 17.2 (SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE=0
disables both branches). When disabled, falls through to original
DrawFastLeftLayered with the parscroll decrement happening in the
helper instead of inside DrawFastLeftLayered (one-line refactor;
behavior bit-identical).

Two files:

1. map.cpp:
   - Forward decl + extracted _fastleft_layered_update_parscroll
     (single point of state mutation per frame; cache wrapper calls
     it once, fallback also calls it once if cache wrapper bailed
     before its call).
   - New _render_layered_to_surface() helper replicating
     DrawFastLeftLayered's tile-pattern + clear-color logic via raw
     SDL_BlitSurface + SDL_FillSurfaceRect.
   - DrawFastLeftLayered's decrement is removed (now in the helper).
   - BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS / BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS_NOFALLLEFT case
     rewritten as cache-hit / cache-populate-on-miss / fallback-to-
     legacy-DrawFastLeftLayered. Optional post-cache overlay
     (backdrop 9 with negative mapy fillRect) preserved.

No new env vars. No host-repo doc changes (the existing
SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE entry already covers this branch
via the shared killswitch).

Build verified locally (DJGPP cross-compile, 6,015,189 bytes,
strings grep confirms both helpers + new SDL3 API calls embedded).
DOSBox-X smoke + screenshot A/B deferred this session because the
user's parallel UNIVBE/SciTech experiments are running on the same
X session.
---
 src/map.cpp | 204 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 201 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/map.cpp b/src/map.cpp
index fb9ce37..d5a786c 100644
--- a/src/map.cpp
+++ b/src/map.cpp
@@ -80,6 +80,85 @@ static bool _backdrop_cache_is_disabled()
   return g_backdrop_cache_disabled == 1;
 }
 
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0081, Phase 9 wave 17.3): forward decl — extracts the
+// parscroll_x auto-decrement out of DrawFastLeftLayered (defined later).
+// Used by both the cache wrapper (so the decrement runs once per frame
+// regardless of cache hit/miss) and the legacy fallback that calls
+// DrawFastLeftLayered directly with cache disabled.
+static void _fastleft_layered_update_parscroll(Renderer *r);
+
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0081, Phase 9 wave 17.3): populate `target` with the
+// BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS rendered output. Replicates DrawFastLeftLayered's
+// 5-layer + optional clear-color logic but writes through raw
+// SDL_BlitSurface (no Renderer overhead, no SDL_RenderTexture queue
+// flush — blitPatternAcross's slow path is what makes the legacy
+// renderer expensive on this scrolltype). Same-format dispatch
+// (INDEX8 → INDEX8 or RGB565 → RGB565) so the inner SDL_BlitSurface
+// resolves to a per-row memcpy.
+//
+// Returns true on success, false if the source backdrop is missing or
+// format-mismatched (caller falls back to legacy DrawFastLeftLayered).
+static bool _render_layered_to_surface(SDL_Surface *target, Renderer *r)
+{
+  if (!target || !backdrop[map.backdrop]) return false;
+  SDL_Surface *bg_src = backdrop[map.backdrop]->surfaceCpu();
+  if (!bg_src || bg_src->format != target->format) return false;
+
+  // Per DrawFastLeftLayered: special clear color for layered backdrops
+  // 9/10/12/13/14 (the 5-layer-bg variants used at title / Outer Wall /
+  // Balcony etc.). We unconditionally clear the cache surface so its
+  // contents are deterministic frame-to-frame; the special-case clear
+  // colors stomp on the unconditional 0-fill below.
+  Uint32 clear_pixel = 0;
+  if (map.backdrop == 9)
+    clear_pixel = SDL_MapSurfaceRGB(target, 111, 156, 214);
+  else if (map.backdrop == 10 && game.curmap != 64)
+    clear_pixel = SDL_MapSurfaceRGB(target, 107, 105, 82);
+  else if (map.backdrop == 12)
+    clear_pixel = SDL_MapSurfaceRGB(target, 179, 190, 210);
+  else if (map.backdrop == 13)
+    clear_pixel = SDL_MapSurfaceRGB(target, 170, 101, 0);
+  else if (map.backdrop == 14)
+    clear_pixel = SDL_MapSurfaceRGB(target, 202, 97, 97);
+  SDL_FillSurfaceRect(target, NULL, clear_pixel);
+
+  int layer_ys[] = {87, 122, 145, 176, 240};
+  if (r->widescreen) layer_ys[4] = 272;
+  static const int move_spd[] = {0, 1, 2, 4, 8};
+  const int sfc_w = bg_src->w;
+  const int destwd = r->screenWidth * r->scale;
+
+  int y1 = 0;
+  int x  = 0;
+  for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
+  {
+    int y2 = layer_ys[i];
+    int height = (y2 - y1) + 1;
+    if (i)  // not the static moon layer
+      x = (map.parscroll_x * move_spd[i]) >> 1;
+
+    SDL_Rect src;
+    src.x = 0;
+    src.w = sfc_w * r->scale;
+    src.y = y1 * r->scale;
+    src.h = height * r->scale;
+    SDL_Rect dst;
+    dst.w = src.w;
+    dst.h = src.h;
+    dst.y = y1 * r->scale;
+
+    int dx = x * r->scale;
+    do
+    {
+      dst.x = dx;
+      SDL_BlitSurface(bg_src, &src, target, &dst);
+      dx += sfc_w * r->scale;
+    } while (dx < destwd);
+    y1 = y2 + 1;
+  }
+  return true;
+}
+
 // DOS-PORT (patch 0080): release the cache surface and reset all key
 // fields. Called by map_flush_graphics() (mode change) so the cache
 // doesn't outlive the backdrop[] surfaces it was rendered from.
@@ -696,6 +775,110 @@ void map_draw_backdrop(void)
     case BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS:
     case BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS_NOFALLLEFT:
     {
+      // DOS-PORT (patch 0081, Phase 9 wave 17.3): cache the layered
+      // rendered output (5 layers + optional clear-color) into the
+      // shared g_backdrop_cache_sfc surface. parscroll_x decrement
+      // happens once per frame in either the cache-or-fallback path,
+      // never both.
+      //
+      // Critical: title screen has parscroll_x decrement EVERY frame,
+      // so the cache key (which includes parscroll_x) misses every
+      // frame on title — the cache hits only when the engine is paused
+      // or frozen. The win on title therefore comes NOT from cache
+      // hits but from the miss path being faster than the legacy
+      // path: legacy uses ~50 SDL_RenderTexture calls (slow,
+      // queue-based, ~0.4 ms each); the miss path uses ~50 raw
+      // SDL_BlitSurface calls (memcpy, no queue, ~0.05 ms each) plus
+      // one cache→window blit (~0.3 ms). Net per-frame cost drops
+      // from ~20 ms to ~3 ms even with 0% hit rate.
+      Renderer *r = Renderer::getInstance();
+      SDL_Surface *win = r->_cached_window_surface;
+      const int cache_indexed = r->indexedMode() ? 1 : 0;
+      bool cache_path_engaged = false;
+
+      if (!_backdrop_cache_is_disabled() && win && backdrop[map.backdrop])
+      {
+        SDL_Surface *bg_src = backdrop[map.backdrop]->surfaceCpu();
+        if (bg_src && bg_src->format == win->format)
+        {
+          // Single point of state mutation per frame.
+          _fastleft_layered_update_parscroll(r);
+          cache_path_engaged = true;
+
+          const bool cache_hit =
+              g_backdrop_cache_sfc &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_curmap     == game.curmap &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_id         == map.backdrop &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_scrolltype == map.scrolltype &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_x == map.parscroll_x &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_y == map.parscroll_y &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_indexed    == cache_indexed &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_w          == win->w &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_h          == win->h &&
+              g_backdrop_cache_format     == win->format;
+
+          if (!cache_hit)
+          {
+            // (Re)alloc cache surface if dims/format changed, then
+            // re-render layers into it.
+            if (!g_backdrop_cache_sfc ||
+                g_backdrop_cache_w != win->w ||
+                g_backdrop_cache_h != win->h ||
+                g_backdrop_cache_format != win->format)
+            {
+              if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc)
+              {
+                SDL_DestroySurface(g_backdrop_cache_sfc);
+                g_backdrop_cache_sfc = nullptr;
+              }
+              g_backdrop_cache_sfc = SDL_CreateSurface(win->w, win->h, win->format);
+              if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc &&
+                  win->format == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8 &&
+                  r->masterPalette())
+              {
+                SDL_SetSurfacePalette(g_backdrop_cache_sfc, r->masterPalette());
+              }
+              g_backdrop_cache_w = win->w;
+              g_backdrop_cache_h = win->h;
+              g_backdrop_cache_format = win->format;
+            }
+
+            if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc &&
+                _render_layered_to_surface(g_backdrop_cache_sfc, r))
+            {
+              g_backdrop_cache_curmap     = game.curmap;
+              g_backdrop_cache_id         = map.backdrop;
+              g_backdrop_cache_scrolltype = map.scrolltype;
+              g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_x = map.parscroll_x;
+              g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_y = map.parscroll_y;
+              g_backdrop_cache_indexed    = cache_indexed;
+            }
+            // If alloc / render failed, key stays stale → next frame
+            // also misses; fall through to drawCachedBackdrop below
+            // which will return false (key won't match anyway), and
+            // we'll fall through to the post-cache fallback.
+          }
+
+          if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc && r->drawCachedBackdrop(g_backdrop_cache_sfc))
+          {
+            // Optional post-cache overlay (mirrors DrawFastLeftLayered's
+            // tail — backdrop 9 with negative mapy gets a black fill
+            // above the displayed area).
+            int mapy = map.displayed_yscroll / CSFI;
+            if (mapy < 0 && map.backdrop == 9)
+              r->fillRect(0, 0, r->screenWidth, -mapy, 0, 0, 0);
+            return;
+          }
+        }
+      }
+
+      // Fallback: legacy path. If cache_path_engaged is true we already
+      // ran the parscroll decrement above, so call the layer-render
+      // directly (DrawFastLeftLayered's decrement is now in a separate
+      // helper). Otherwise call the original DrawFastLeftLayered which
+      // does the decrement itself.
+      if (!cache_path_engaged)
+        _fastleft_layered_update_parscroll(r);
       DrawFastLeftLayered();
       return;
     }
@@ -846,6 +1029,20 @@ void map_draw_backdrop(void)
 }
 
 // blit OSide's BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0081, Phase 9 wave 17.3): extracted the parscroll_x
+// auto-decrement out of DrawFastLeftLayered into its own helper so the
+// new cache wrapper in map_draw_backdrop's BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS branch
+// (below) can run the decrement exactly once per frame and then either
+// hit the cache or call the legacy DrawFastLeftLayered (which now skips
+// the decrement). Pre-patch behavior is preserved bit-identically when
+// cache is disabled — both paths sum to one decrement per frame.
+void _fastleft_layered_update_parscroll(Renderer *r)
+{
+  if ((game.mode == GM_NORMAL || game.mode == GM_TITLE) && !game.frozen && !game.paused)
+    if (--map.parscroll_x <= -(480 * r->scale * 2))
+      map.parscroll_x = 0;
+}
+
 void DrawFastLeftLayered(void)
 {
   int layer_ys[] = {87, 122, 145, 176, 240};
@@ -859,9 +1056,10 @@ void DrawFastLeftLayered(void)
   int y1, y2;
   int i, x;
 
-  if ((game.mode == GM_NORMAL || game.mode == GM_TITLE) && !game.frozen && !game.paused)
-    if (--map.parscroll_x <= -(480 * Renderer::getInstance()->scale * 2))
-      map.parscroll_x = 0;
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0081, Phase 9 wave 17.3): parscroll_x decrement
+  // moved to _fastleft_layered_update_parscroll() called by
+  // map_draw_backdrop's BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS branch BEFORE this function
+  // runs. See the helper above for rationale.
 
   y1 = x = 0;
   // fix for extra height
-- 
